Butchers and meat traders in Nanyuki and its environs have hailed the decision by the Laikipia county government, to procure a state of the art equipment  for the Nanyuki slaughter house. According to Nanyuki Butchers Union, Chairman Christopher Mithamo, the abattre has had a very difficult time since all the equipment had broken down. The new equipment will help improve efficiency at the abattre The slaughter house that is one of the busiest in the region, can now comfortably handle 600 animals per day. 